overview: The user started by pointing out that they had five Vercel projects
  for their  app when there should only be one. I
  identified that these were duplicate projects likely created by importing the
  same GitHub repository multiple times. I then proceeded to delete the four
  duplicate projects using the Vercel CLI, ensuring only the main
   project remained. After the cleanup, the user asked for
  guidance on setting up a development environment with a separate domain and
  whether a separate branch was necessary. I recommended creating a
  branch, configuring branch-specific environment variables in Vercel, and
  optionally assigning a custom subdomain to the  branch's deployments.
  This approach leverages Vercel's preview deployment features for a clean
  development workflow.
